1
00:00:03,800 --> 00:00:07,160
(WeTV Original)

2
00:00:09,530 --> 00:00:11,410
♪Way Way to You♪

3
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:18,400
♪Way Way to You♪

4
00:00:27,050 --> 00:00:30,600
♪On My Way to You♪

5
00:00:30,760 --> 00:00:35,080
=Way To You=

6
00:00:35,080 --> 00:00:36,440
(Highlights of this episode:
Special Guest Mentors)

7
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:39,620
(Sweet moments)

8
00:00:39,620 --> 00:00:41,180
(Contestants forming new teams)

9
00:00:41,310 --> 00:00:42,640
- Okay, Deaw.
- Thank you.

10
00:00:42,640 --> 00:00:44,920
Take the flower
and give it to your new partner.

11
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:46,270
Can I touch you?

12
00:00:46,270 --> 00:00:46,690
Hmm.

13
00:00:47,240 --> 00:00:49,540
For now, I don't really want
to separate from him.

14
00:00:52,140 --> 00:00:55,000
At that moment,
no one came to mind because...

15
00:00:55,320 --> 00:00:56,790
You're late.

16
00:00:57,390 --> 00:00:59,660
I think Cannon and I
have good chemistry.

17
00:01:04,970 --> 00:01:06,690
I feel like we balance each other well.

18
00:01:06,690 --> 00:01:08,690
At that time
I was actually a bit nervous.

19
00:01:08,690 --> 00:01:10,160
Because honestly,

20
00:01:10,160 --> 00:01:14,000
I think Tai is someone
who could work really well with me.

21
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,970
(How will they form their teams
in the end?)

22
00:01:26,990 --> 00:01:29,340
This week's evaluation theme is

23
00:01:29,340 --> 00:01:30,320
acting.

24
00:01:30,320 --> 00:01:32,480
For this round, we've specially invited

25
00:01:32,480 --> 00:01:33,830
two well-known Thai actors,

26
00:01:33,830 --> 00:01:35,230
Peat and Fort.

27
00:01:35,700 --> 00:01:41,460
(Yesterday)

28
00:01:45,745 --> 00:01:47,231
I don't love you.

29
00:01:48,337 --> 00:01:49,188
Understand?

30
00:01:53,250 --> 00:01:54,340
Yes.

31
00:01:54,820 --> 00:01:56,550
Now, everyone...

32
00:01:56,550 --> 00:02:00,130
I have here in my hand

33
00:02:00,130 --> 00:02:02,020
(Half of the list of names?)
half of the list of names.

34
00:02:02,020 --> 00:02:04,520
Those whose names are called
can receive a rose from us

35
00:02:04,520 --> 00:02:06,290
and give it to their new partner.

36
00:02:06,290 --> 00:02:09,070
(Choosing new partners again)

37
00:02:12,330 --> 00:02:13,730
Can I say something?

38
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:15,930
(Very happy)

39
00:02:15,930 --> 00:02:18,790
At that moment,
no one came to mind

40
00:02:18,790 --> 00:02:20,080
(Jony, bye-bye)
because

41
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:22,260
normally we stay in the same room,

42
00:02:22,260 --> 00:02:26,210
but communication between us
is actually quite difficult.

43
00:02:26,210 --> 00:02:26,710
(Don't laugh)

44
00:02:26,710 --> 00:02:28,630
Alright, let's begin.

45
00:02:28,630 --> 00:02:30,520
We'll start with the first person.

46
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:32,840
(Who will choose first?)

47
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:34,390
Deaw.

48
00:02:34,660 --> 00:02:36,910
(Deaw chooses first)
Come to the front.

49
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:41,260
Because last time, your dance received

50
00:02:41,260 --> 00:02:43,640
the highest internal vote.

51
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:45,440
(After last week's dance evaluation)
So right now you have three votes.

52
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:49,030
You can give them to the person
you think performed best today.

53
00:02:49,030 --> 00:02:51,600
I'll give it to my good partner, Deaw.

54
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:55,630
Deaw.

55
00:02:57,170 --> 00:02:58,820
(Voted No.1
in the internal dance assessment)

56
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,320
- Okay, Deaw.
- Thank you.

57
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:02,580
Take the flower
and give it to your new partner.

58
00:03:05,260 --> 00:03:07,290
(Nervous)

59
00:03:07,910 --> 00:03:10,780
(Will Deaw choose Tai?)

60
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:12,940
(Yesterday afternoon)
Choose the partner

61
00:03:12,940 --> 00:03:14,750
you want to work with next week.

62
00:03:14,760 --> 00:03:16,860
(Choosing a new Chinese partner)

63
00:03:16,860 --> 00:03:18,660
Because honestly,

64
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:25,290
I think Tai is someone
who could work really well with me.

65
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:27,040
But actually, I think

66
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:29,780
I might change partners.

67
00:03:29,780 --> 00:03:32,320
This is only our first week here.

68
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:35,290
I feel like there are still many people
I'd like to get to know.

69
00:03:35,290 --> 00:03:36,990
Everyone thinks differently,

70
00:03:36,990 --> 00:03:38,280
and everyone has their own style.

71
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:40,320
I haven't really had the chance
to get to know the others yet.

72
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:41,940
(Wanting to meet new people)

73
00:03:46,110 --> 00:03:50,490
Actually, I might choose U.Jay or Kai.

74
00:03:50,490 --> 00:03:52,040
(People on his mind: U.Jay and Kai)

75
00:03:52,460 --> 00:03:53,320
Alright.

76
00:03:53,740 --> 00:03:59,300
(Who will he choose? Kai or U.Jay?)

77
00:04:00,210 --> 00:04:02,010
(Heartbroken)

78
00:04:02,010 --> 00:04:03,410
(Don't touch me!)

79
00:04:06,130 --> 00:04:08,500
(Deaw chooses U.Jay) U.Jay.

80
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:12,870
Hello.

81
00:04:14,270 --> 00:04:15,020
Hello.

82
00:04:15,740 --> 00:04:18,470
I also want to try working with U.Jay.

83
00:04:18,470 --> 00:04:21,930
Because we need to act this time,
and he seems to speak Thai too.

84
00:04:22,410 --> 00:04:23,270
You're out.

85
00:04:24,780 --> 00:04:25,940
You're out.

86
00:04:25,940 --> 00:04:26,440
(Eliminated)

87
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:28,240
You're out.

88
00:04:28,390 --> 00:04:29,190
You're out.

89
00:04:29,260 --> 00:04:31,940
You can switch seats now
and sit with your new partner.

90
00:04:32,470 --> 00:04:33,370
I'm out.

91
00:04:33,370 --> 00:04:34,480
Alright, I'm out.

92
00:04:36,100 --> 00:04:37,840
(Turns out I'm the joke)

93
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:40,060
My first reaction was surprise.

94
00:04:40,060 --> 00:04:42,760
I didn't expect Deaw to choose me.

95
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:45,060
I'm very grateful for his trust,

96
00:04:45,060 --> 00:04:47,710
and I'll do my best

97
00:04:47,710 --> 00:04:49,300
to support him,

98
00:04:49,300 --> 00:04:50,400
so we can improve together

99
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:52,460
and win first place again next time.

100
00:04:52,740 --> 00:04:53,880
(Deaw and U.Jay
successfully form a team)

101
00:04:54,140 --> 00:04:55,180
Thank you.

102
00:04:56,940 --> 00:04:59,650
Alright, next is Leo.

103
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:01,260
(Second pick: Leo)

104
00:05:01,640 --> 00:05:02,810
Thank you.

105
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:07,660
Okay, give the flower
to your new partner.

106
00:05:08,110 --> 00:05:10,060
(Leo begins choosing)

107
00:05:13,230 --> 00:05:15,130
I think Leo will choose me.

108
00:05:15,130 --> 00:05:16,160
We already promised

109
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:18,630
to go all the way to the top together.

110
00:05:18,630 --> 00:05:19,440
Go on.

111
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:23,320
No... No.

112
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:26,050
(Bye-bye, Jony)

113
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:29,770
(The two brothers get dramatic)
Jony, we've both been abandoned.

114
00:05:29,770 --> 00:05:31,840
(Sharing the same fate)
We've been abandoned.

115
00:05:32,940 --> 00:05:34,940
(Who will Leo choose?)

116
00:05:35,940 --> 00:05:37,860
(Leo chooses Kai)

117
00:05:37,940 --> 00:05:40,070
Bye-bye.

118
00:05:40,370 --> 00:05:41,570
(Confused)

119
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:44,000
Kai.

120
00:05:44,500 --> 00:05:45,370
(Leo chose Kai yesterday)
Why?

121
00:05:45,370 --> 00:05:48,040
This time,
language is more important to me.

122
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:54,020
Because for acting, communication
is the most important thing.

123
00:05:54,020 --> 00:05:55,420
Because I think

124
00:05:55,420 --> 00:05:59,410
Kai can speak English.

125
00:05:59,410 --> 00:06:03,960
If we partner up for acting,
it should be easier.

126
00:06:03,960 --> 00:06:06,220
I was very surprised Leo chose me.

127
00:06:06,220 --> 00:06:07,000
Because I always felt

128
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:09,270
our interactions weren't that many.

129
00:06:09,270 --> 00:06:10,620
I'd like to give it a try too.

130
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:11,160
Yeah give it a try.

131
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:13,520
After all, acting
is a completely different experience.

132
00:06:13,520 --> 00:06:16,700
Maybe this could spark something new,

133
00:06:16,700 --> 00:06:19,500
(Looking forward to new sparks)
or maybe we'll make new good friends.

134
00:06:19,660 --> 00:06:20,940
Good luck.

135
00:06:21,940 --> 00:06:23,000
You're out.

136
00:06:23,210 --> 00:06:25,120
(Got kicked out again)

137
00:06:25,310 --> 00:06:26,360
Maybe I'll sit in the middle.

138
00:06:26,580 --> 00:06:28,220
(Let me join you guys)

139
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:30,550
In the middle?

140
00:06:30,970 --> 00:06:32,650
(Give me a moment to recover)

141
00:06:32,730 --> 00:06:33,890
I feel like a third-wheel.

142
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:37,460
(Leo and Kai successfully form a team)

143
00:06:38,490 --> 00:06:40,840
Next is Tai.

144
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:43,260
(Third pick: Tai)

145
00:06:44,660 --> 00:06:47,160
Alright, Tai.

146
00:06:48,030 --> 00:06:50,430
(Who will Tai choose?)

147
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:51,450
Ryu.

148
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:54,000
(Do you need something?)

149
00:06:56,660 --> 00:06:57,720
You scared me.

150
00:06:58,310 --> 00:06:59,160
Ryu.

151
00:06:59,160 --> 00:07:00,090
What's up?

152
00:07:01,750 --> 00:07:04,130
(Tai chooses Ryu)
Thank you.

153
00:07:04,210 --> 00:07:04,800
I have to move again?

154
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:05,780
(Taking the initiative)
No, no.

155
00:07:11,770 --> 00:07:13,840
I'm very happy Tai chose me.

156
00:07:13,840 --> 00:07:15,410
Actually,
I've always wanted to partner with Tai.

157
00:07:15,410 --> 00:07:17,000
Because I feel

158
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,750
he's very energetic.

159
00:07:19,170 --> 00:07:20,270
I'm kind of low on energy.

160
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,660
Maybe he can help me with that.

161
00:07:23,620 --> 00:07:25,330
You're out.

162
00:07:25,330 --> 00:07:26,340
Out.

163
00:07:26,790 --> 00:07:30,630
I think I can help make him
a bit more interesting.

164
00:07:31,060 --> 00:07:33,920
I want to bring out that fun side of him
and show it to everyone.

165
00:07:34,140 --> 00:07:36,260
(Tai and Ryu successfully form a team)

166
00:07:37,250 --> 00:07:39,490
Next is Cannon.

167
00:07:39,490 --> 00:07:40,700
(Fourth pick: Cannon)

168
00:07:40,700 --> 00:07:41,840
Cannon.

169
00:07:42,210 --> 00:07:43,820
(Staring)

170
00:07:45,880 --> 00:07:47,240
Alright, here you go.

171
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:50,680
(Who will Cannon choose?)

172
00:07:51,340 --> 00:07:53,610
I think Cannon and I
have good chemistry.

173
00:07:54,490 --> 00:07:54,900
Even though we only had

174
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:57,750
(Reselecting partners yesterday)
a short time to get to know each other,

175
00:07:57,750 --> 00:07:59,040
during that process

176
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:01,780
I felt really comfortable
being around him.

177
00:08:01,780 --> 00:08:02,920
(Comfortable)

178
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:03,460
Yeah.

179
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:05,150
Any other hesitations?

180
00:08:05,270 --> 00:08:05,940
No.

181
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:07,230
(No hesitation)

182
00:08:19,650 --> 00:08:21,370
Do you think he'll choose someone else?

183
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:23,150
Probably.

184
00:08:26,050 --> 00:08:26,870
What?

185
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:29,480
Hello.

186
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:30,260
What's your name?

187
00:08:30,410 --> 00:08:31,290
Eugene.

188
00:08:31,940 --> 00:08:32,940
Cannon.

189
00:08:38,630 --> 00:08:40,860
Being with him feels really comfortable.

190
00:08:41,740 --> 00:08:43,400
He's the one for me.

191
00:08:43,580 --> 00:08:45,740
I think Cannon...

192
00:08:47,940 --> 00:08:49,300
Any other hesitations?

193
00:08:49,580 --> 00:08:50,340
No.

194
00:08:51,190 --> 00:08:53,820
I think Cannon and I
have good chemistry.

195
00:08:54,230 --> 00:08:55,930
This time, I choose Pippin.

196
00:09:15,510 --> 00:09:16,650
You're out.

197
00:09:21,490 --> 00:09:25,330
Finally, the last one, Poom.

198
00:09:25,610 --> 00:09:27,280
(Poom chooses last)
Looks like there's only one option.

199
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:30,270
Alright.

200
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:35,500
(Poom chooses Jony. No other option)

201
00:09:36,190 --> 00:09:37,670
Who do you want to choose?

202
00:09:37,670 --> 00:09:38,980
(Choosing partners yesterday)

203
00:09:38,980 --> 00:09:41,610
(Choosing U.Jay)
Can I choose him?

204
00:09:42,050 --> 00:09:44,130
(Teaming up failed)
He's already been chosen. Pick again.

205
00:09:44,130 --> 00:09:44,800
Alright.

206
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:46,890
(Choosing Eugene)
He's also taken.

207
00:09:46,890 --> 00:09:48,080
(Failed again)
Alright.

208
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:49,950
(Failed)
He's taken.

209
00:09:50,340 --> 00:09:51,080
Okay.

210
00:09:51,190 --> 00:09:52,110
Taken.

211
00:09:52,110 --> 00:09:54,150
(Failed again)
Taken? Okay.

212
00:09:55,310 --> 00:09:56,610
(Choosing Tai)

213
00:09:56,850 --> 00:09:58,420
(Hoping)

214
00:09:58,420 --> 00:09:58,930
(Please...)

215
00:09:58,930 --> 00:10:00,420
Sorry.

216
00:10:00,430 --> 00:10:02,010
(Teaming up failed)

217
00:10:02,010 --> 00:10:02,650
Okay.

218
00:10:05,850 --> 00:10:08,840
(Only Jony left)

219
00:10:09,690 --> 00:10:12,530
Please pick it up.

220
00:10:16,580 --> 00:10:17,610
How do I feel about this?

221
00:10:17,610 --> 00:10:20,160
If I have no choice,

222
00:10:20,990 --> 00:10:26,230
then within the limited options,
I'll do my best.

223
00:10:26,460 --> 00:10:28,510
If he doesn't cooperate,

224
00:10:28,510 --> 00:10:31,450
I'll simply tell him
what he needs to do.

225
00:10:31,450 --> 00:10:33,780
Whether he does it or not is up to him.

226
00:10:34,220 --> 00:10:36,490
But I'll do my part

227
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:38,460
and present the best result possible.

228
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:41,300
Alright.

229
00:10:41,300 --> 00:10:42,520
Thank you.

230
00:10:43,150 --> 00:10:45,090
(All contestants
have chosen their new partners)

231
00:10:45,090 --> 00:10:49,170
Now we can see that all teams
are Chinese–Thai pairs.

232
00:10:49,980 --> 00:10:53,650
Actually, this week's evaluation
is all about communication.

233
00:10:53,650 --> 00:10:55,250
(Communication is the key)

234
00:10:55,250 --> 00:10:56,420
Can you guess what it is?

235
00:10:56,850 --> 00:10:57,510
Debate.

236
00:10:58,010 --> 00:10:59,700
(Debate?)

237
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:00,940
Acting.

238
00:11:01,020 --> 00:11:02,300
Ding dong.

239
00:11:03,090 --> 00:11:04,880
Here's our rule.

240
00:11:04,880 --> 00:11:06,980
We will provide

241
00:11:06,980 --> 00:11:08,570
(Three different TV scripts)
three scripts.

242
00:11:08,570 --> 00:11:13,060
But each script
can only be chosen by two teams.

243
00:11:13,060 --> 00:11:16,910
(Each script can be performed
by up to two teams only)

244
00:11:17,070 --> 00:11:21,130
The first script is sci-fi
with time travel.

245
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:26,930
Time travel.

246
00:11:27,220 --> 00:11:29,150
There are two main characters.

247
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:30,590
One is Youyou.

248
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:31,930
Youyou.

249
00:11:31,930 --> 00:11:38,110
Youyou is a ghost from the past
who travels to the present.

250
00:11:40,910 --> 00:11:41,790
A ghost.

251
00:11:41,790 --> 00:11:44,690
The other is Xiaoye.

252
00:11:44,690 --> 00:11:47,860
Xiaoye is just an ordinary student,

253
00:11:47,860 --> 00:11:52,400
but he's being haunted
by the ghost Youyou.

254
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:53,440
(This plot feels familiar)

255
00:11:53,890 --> 00:11:54,830
I think I've seen this before.

256
00:11:54,830 --> 00:11:55,730
I feel like I've watched this.

257
00:11:56,650 --> 00:11:57,410
I know this one.

258
00:11:57,410 --> 00:11:58,230
I've seen it.

259
00:11:58,450 --> 00:11:59,240
I like this.

260
00:11:59,240 --> 00:11:59,680
(I like this)

261
00:11:59,680 --> 00:12:00,500
Do you like this one?

262
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:02,410
This one is very interesting.

263
00:12:02,410 --> 00:12:03,040
Okay.

264
00:12:03,220 --> 00:12:04,530
This one's not bad.

265
00:12:04,530 --> 00:12:06,590
(Also interested in this script)
It should be a comedy.

266
00:12:06,590 --> 00:12:07,340
Is it funny?

267
00:12:07,340 --> 00:12:08,420
A little funny.

268
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:11,190
I'm not sure,

269
00:12:12,350 --> 00:12:15,120
but from my experience,

270
00:12:15,130 --> 00:12:17,010
(Comedy tests acting more)
comedy is harder than drama.

271
00:12:21,380 --> 00:12:23,990
The character can't laugh.

272
00:12:24,070 --> 00:12:27,860
(You can't laugh while acting)
You have to truly believe

273
00:12:27,860 --> 00:12:30,610
in the character.

274
00:12:30,700 --> 00:12:35,050
So I think comedy is harder.

275
00:12:35,620 --> 00:12:36,420
I see.

276
00:12:36,450 --> 00:12:42,830
Alright.
The second script is a bit cute.

277
00:12:44,300 --> 00:12:45,610
Galaxy Garden.

278
00:12:45,610 --> 00:12:50,080
This drama tells the story
of Dao Mingwu and Baicai.

