but we lost the challenge.

557
00:24:56,250 --> 00:24:58,350
The biggest problem between us

558
00:24:58,350 --> 00:25:00,220
was still communication.

559
00:25:00,220 --> 00:25:01,900
I had a lot of ideas,

560
00:25:01,900 --> 00:25:06,230
but I couldn't express them
to Cannon in time.

561
00:25:06,230 --> 00:25:07,770
So that's a bit of a pity.

562
00:25:08,540 --> 00:25:09,580
At first I felt a little upset,

563
00:25:09,580 --> 00:25:11,700
because I had already imagined

564
00:25:11,700 --> 00:25:13,710
how I wanted to perform it.

565
00:25:13,710 --> 00:25:15,570
But since we didn't get it,

566
00:25:15,570 --> 00:25:17,610
maybe it just
didn't fit my character that well.

567
00:25:17,610 --> 00:25:21,230
I think this will help
improve my acting skills

568
00:25:21,230 --> 00:25:23,060
because I haven't tried this kind
of role before.

569
00:25:23,060 --> 00:25:25,170
Trying different styles

570
00:25:25,170 --> 00:25:27,730
can help improve my acting.

571
00:25:28,070 --> 00:25:30,990
Alright, let's move on
to the next script.

572
00:25:31,130 --> 00:25:32,500
The second script.

573
00:25:32,500 --> 00:25:34,180
The second script is

574
00:25:34,180 --> 00:25:35,540
"Galaxy Garden".

575
00:25:35,640 --> 00:25:38,320
"Galaxy Garden".

576
00:25:38,730 --> 00:25:40,440
Let's wait a moment.

577
00:25:40,630 --> 00:25:42,930
If more than two teams want it,
I don't want it to turn into...

578
00:25:42,930 --> 00:25:45,100
Yeah, I understand.
I don't want to battle for it.

579
00:25:46,200 --> 00:25:47,270
Please raise your hands.

580
00:25:52,210 --> 00:25:52,780
No one?

581
00:25:52,780 --> 00:25:54,330
Then let us go for it.

582
00:25:54,330 --> 00:25:55,260
(One vote for "Galaxy Garden")

583
00:25:55,930 --> 00:25:57,860
- Do you want this one?
- Yes.

584
00:25:57,860 --> 00:25:58,740
(Two votes for "Galaxy Garden")

585
00:25:58,740 --> 00:25:59,370
One...

586
00:25:59,860 --> 00:26:00,880
Oh two votes?

587
00:26:00,880 --> 00:26:03,540
Two groups have chosen "Galaxy Garden".

588
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:05,690
(Only two teams chose it,
so they automatically get the script.)

589
00:26:05,690 --> 00:26:07,690
That means

590
00:26:07,690 --> 00:26:11,930
the remaining two teams
will perform "The CEO Falls for Me".

591
00:26:12,380 --> 00:26:14,080
(The remaining two teams
automatically get the CEO script.)

592
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:21,620
(Final performance groups)

593
00:26:31,820 --> 00:26:35,100
Next, we'll play an acting game

594
00:26:35,100 --> 00:26:38,440
to help everyone get more familiar
with each other.

595
00:26:38,660 --> 00:26:39,930
(A fun interaction game)

596
00:26:39,930 --> 00:26:42,500
The first game is staring
into each other's eyes.

597
00:26:42,500 --> 00:26:45,290
We'll demonstrate it first.

598
00:26:45,820 --> 00:26:46,640
Okay.

599
00:26:46,640 --> 00:26:50,080
Let us show you a quick example.

600
00:26:55,060 --> 00:26:57,300
(Chemistry Test Game 1: Eye Contact)

601
00:26:59,830 --> 00:27:03,140
(Pairs must hold hands
and look at each other for 30 seconds)

602
00:27:04,040 --> 00:27:05,690
One, two, three.

603
00:27:05,690 --> 00:27:06,750
(Challenge begins)

604
00:27:06,800 --> 00:27:08,780
♪I guess I'm going through a phase♪

605
00:27:08,780 --> 00:27:10,370
♪I'm feeling kinda low♪

606
00:27:10,370 --> 00:27:13,410
♪I never leave the house
but I'm not home♪

607
00:27:13,410 --> 00:27:16,010
♪Everything is turning upside down♪

608
00:27:16,010 --> 00:27:20,030
♪Maybe we're just butterflies,
butterflies♪

609
00:27:20,030 --> 00:27:22,370
♪Going through a chrysalis♪

610
00:27:22,370 --> 00:27:26,350
♪Don't you ever wonder why, wonder why♪

611
00:27:26,690 --> 00:27:29,710
♪We've been going through all this♪
(This is too sweet)

612
00:27:29,710 --> 00:27:33,080
♪Maybe there's a cocoon
around the world♪

613
00:27:33,080 --> 00:27:35,950
♪And we're all dying just
to break through♪

614
00:27:35,950 --> 00:27:39,870
♪'Cause we'll be butterflies,
butterflies♪

615
00:27:39,870 --> 00:27:42,030
♪Brand new♪

616
00:27:45,340 --> 00:27:49,130
♪We won't even remember this♪

617
00:27:52,150 --> 00:27:54,230
(So sweet)

618
00:28:00,630 --> 00:28:01,510
So close.

619
00:28:01,510 --> 00:28:05,000
♪Maybe we're just butterflies,
butterflies♪

620
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:09,600
♪Oh, we'll be butterflies♪

621
00:28:09,600 --> 00:28:12,740
♪Butterflies, butterflies♪

622
00:28:12,740 --> 00:28:14,830
Alright.

623
00:28:17,780 --> 00:28:19,870
About that 30 seconds
of eye contact just now,

624
00:28:19,870 --> 00:28:24,470
I felt like
he looked especially radiant today.

625
00:28:25,480 --> 00:28:29,030
Everything about him seemed
to be glowing.

626
00:28:32,220 --> 00:28:33,990
For me,

627
00:28:33,990 --> 00:28:36,230
those 30 seconds felt like

628
00:28:36,930 --> 00:28:39,590
he's still the same
as when we first met.

629
00:28:39,590 --> 00:28:42,890
It made me feel like we're getting
to know each other better day by day.

630
00:28:43,310 --> 00:28:46,760
And we just watched our new drama
last night,

631
00:28:46,760 --> 00:28:49,490
so just now it almost felt like

632
00:28:49,690 --> 00:28:52,550
Veir was inside him.

633
00:28:53,270 --> 00:28:55,000
(Clip from "Yesterday")

634
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:56,040
How about this?

635
00:28:58,200 --> 00:28:59,210
That's very clear.

636
00:29:09,490 --> 00:29:11,690
Let's try it this way.

637
00:29:11,830 --> 00:29:13,220
(Talking and exchanging experience)
Can I hold your hand?

638
00:29:13,220 --> 00:29:16,120
Can you give me your hand
so I can feel it?

639
00:29:16,300 --> 00:29:17,480
Your hands are warm.

640
00:29:17,480 --> 00:29:19,110
Yeah, you can feel the warmth.

641
00:29:19,690 --> 00:29:21,850
Let's perform first, okay?

642
00:29:21,850 --> 00:29:22,800
(Really?)
Again?

643
00:29:22,800 --> 00:29:24,670
You don't want to go first?

644
00:29:24,670 --> 00:29:25,460
Do you want to?

645
00:29:26,010 --> 00:29:27,500
(Are we going up to perform?)

646
00:29:27,760 --> 00:29:29,830
(First group: Leo & Kai)

647
00:29:31,310 --> 00:29:32,660
They're first.

648
00:29:34,370 --> 00:29:35,200
Don't laugh.

649
00:29:39,220 --> 00:29:41,940
(Challenge begins)

650
00:29:51,630 --> 00:29:53,760
I was actually a little nervous.

651
00:29:53,760 --> 00:29:54,390
Because

652
00:29:54,390 --> 00:29:58,490
I'm still not very familiar with Leo.

653
00:30:08,230 --> 00:30:09,000
Alright.

654
00:30:10,530 --> 00:30:12,150
(You go first.)

655
00:30:12,880 --> 00:30:14,790
(Waiting)

656
00:30:15,360 --> 00:30:16,900
First, just from his appearance,

657
00:30:17,280 --> 00:30:19,430
(Looking again)
his features are very defined,

658
00:30:19,430 --> 00:30:21,210
and his eyes have a slight bluish tint.

659
00:30:21,480 --> 00:30:23,400
His hair color also suits him very well.

660
00:30:23,540 --> 00:30:25,530
And in his eyes,

661
00:30:25,930 --> 00:30:28,130
I can see a kind of gentleness.

662
00:30:28,230 --> 00:30:30,710
(Can't hide the smile)

663
00:30:34,490 --> 00:30:36,510
When I look at him,

664
00:30:36,510 --> 00:30:39,270
I can see that he has

665
00:30:39,550 --> 00:30:41,730
(Determined)
very determined eyes.

666
00:30:41,730 --> 00:30:44,460
(Detail-oriented)
He pays a lot of attention to detail.

667
00:30:44,460 --> 00:30:48,080
(Charming)
He's also a very charming person.

668
00:30:57,590 --> 00:30:58,320
Let's go.

669
00:30:58,600 --> 00:30:59,100
Okay.

670
00:30:59,100 --> 00:31:00,460
(Second group: Ryu & Tai)

671
00:31:00,460 --> 00:31:01,150
Wake up.

672
00:31:01,310 --> 00:31:02,030
Wake up.

673
00:31:02,520 --> 00:31:03,500
Wake up.

674
00:31:12,410 --> 00:31:14,470
(They crack up immediately)

675
00:31:14,470 --> 00:31:16,370
(Prediction)
I think they're going to fail.

676
00:31:18,870 --> 00:31:20,180
(Deep breath)

677
00:31:23,450 --> 00:31:24,660
Take a deep breath.

678
00:31:25,830 --> 00:31:28,200
(Challenge begins)

679
00:31:28,200 --> 00:31:29,990
(Can't last three seconds)

680
00:31:34,550 --> 00:31:37,190
(Focus.)
(Alright.)

681
00:31:39,140 --> 00:31:42,040
(Good luck)
Come on.

682
00:31:43,270 --> 00:31:44,980
(Let's pass in one try)

683
00:31:47,640 --> 00:31:48,630
So awkward.

684
00:31:57,680 --> 00:31:58,750
(Why?) Why?

685
00:32:00,150 --> 00:32:03,630
(Second attempt)

686
00:32:03,630 --> 00:32:04,380
Hello.

687
00:32:11,710 --> 00:32:12,520
What's going on?

688
00:32:14,110 --> 00:32:15,810
- Let's do it properly.
- Okay.

689
00:32:15,810 --> 00:32:17,510
We can do it.

690
00:32:17,510 --> 00:32:18,550
We've got this. Let's focus.

691
00:32:21,370 --> 00:32:22,590
(Maybe we can't)

692
00:32:22,590 --> 00:32:23,750
What happened?

693
00:32:25,460 --> 00:32:26,440
(The savior arrives)

694
00:32:26,440 --> 00:32:27,750
Stand properly.

695
00:32:27,750 --> 00:32:28,720
Hold hands.

696
00:32:29,870 --> 00:32:30,770
Okay.

697
00:32:35,470 --> 00:32:38,030
(Hold it in)

698
00:32:38,030 --> 00:32:41,830
(I can do this)

699
00:32:49,480 --> 00:32:52,550
(Leaves satisfied)

700
00:32:59,920 --> 00:33:01,310
(Don't laugh. Hold it in)

701
00:33:08,010 --> 00:33:08,850
Okay.

702
00:33:10,870 --> 00:33:12,990
(In sync)

703
00:33:15,150 --> 00:33:16,960
It was a bit difficult.

704
00:33:17,900 --> 00:33:19,640
Because his face...

705
00:33:19,640 --> 00:33:20,930
(Is naturally funny)

706
00:33:23,040 --> 00:33:23,760
Is it over?

707
00:33:28,860 --> 00:33:29,430
Is it over?

708
00:33:29,440 --> 00:33:31,050
What about you?

709
00:33:31,320 --> 00:33:32,100
- What about you?
- Me?

710
00:33:32,110 --> 00:33:32,840
What about you?

711
00:33:33,260 --> 00:33:35,210
At first I laughed when I saw him

712
00:33:35,450 --> 00:33:37,200
not because he looks funny,

713
00:33:37,320 --> 00:33:38,760
but because in our daily life,

714
00:33:38,760 --> 00:33:40,440
we have a lot of funny moments.

715
00:33:40,450 --> 00:33:41,950
So when I looked at him,
those memories came back,

716
00:33:41,950 --> 00:33:44,040
and once I think of them,
I can't help but laugh,

717
00:33:44,040 --> 00:33:45,870
but later we finally calmed down.

718
00:33:45,870 --> 00:33:47,990
We held our hands loosely at first,

719
00:33:48,140 --> 00:33:49,700
but then we slowly held on tighter.

720
00:33:49,700 --> 00:33:52,430
It felt like
we were connecting a little.

721
00:33:52,630 --> 00:33:55,050
Then he suddenly squeezed my hand again,

722
00:33:55,050 --> 00:33:56,930
and I remembered something funny

723
00:33:56,930 --> 00:33:57,830
so I couldn't hold it in anymore.

724
00:34:01,360 --> 00:34:03,650
I think the bigger issue was
that they couldn't focus.

725
00:34:03,650 --> 00:34:05,970
Both of them lost concentration.

726
00:34:05,970 --> 00:34:07,320
Just now I stepped out

727
00:34:07,910 --> 00:34:09,890
because I thought if I did that,

728
00:34:09,890 --> 00:34:11,390
it might help them focus again.

729
00:34:12,580 --> 00:34:14,290
For tomorrow's script,

730
00:34:14,290 --> 00:34:17,130
spend more time working on your roles.

731
00:34:17,130 --> 00:34:18,370
During the performance tomorrow,

732
00:34:18,370 --> 00:34:19,950
try to fully immerse yourself
in the character.

733
00:34:19,950 --> 00:34:21,250
Don't think about anything else.

734
00:34:21,390 --> 00:34:22,450
It should help a lot.

735
00:34:23,390 --> 00:34:24,570
Thank you, teacher.

736
00:34:27,900 --> 00:34:29,060
We're not professional enough.

737
00:34:29,610 --> 00:34:30,080
It's okay.

738
00:34:30,080 --> 00:34:31,470
(Comforting each other)
It's okay.

739
00:34:31,470 --> 00:34:31,860
Let's go.

740
00:34:31,860 --> 00:34:33,730
(Third group: Tron & Eugene)

741
00:34:34,110 --> 00:34:34,950
Can I touch you?

742
00:34:34,950 --> 00:34:35,370
Sure.

743
00:34:37,370 --> 00:34:38,260
Are you hot?

744
00:34:41,500 --> 00:34:44,050
(Challenge begins)

745
00:34:51,300 --> 00:34:52,490
When we first looked at each other,

746
00:34:52,490 --> 00:34:54,250
I was actually pretty nervous.

747
00:34:54,250 --> 00:34:55,160
Really nervous.

748
00:34:56,560 --> 00:34:58,900
There was a moment
when I almost laughed.

749
00:34:59,890 --> 00:35:01,230
Then Tron gripped my hand

750
00:35:01,230 --> 00:35:02,390
really tightly.

751
00:35:03,640 --> 00:35:06,050
Gradually, I calmed down.

752
00:35:09,240 --> 00:35:10,170
(Devil persona activated)

753
00:35:10,170 --> 00:35:11,350
Why are you laughing?

754
00:35:12,840 --> 00:35:14,610
(Angel persona returns)

755
00:35:20,350 --> 00:35:20,920
What?

756
00:35:21,070 --> 00:35:21,860
(Still not satisfied)

757
00:35:21,860 --> 00:35:22,450
Is it over?

758
00:35:22,450 --> 00:35:23,030
Alright.

759
00:35:26,500 --> 00:35:27,650
(Waiting)

760
00:35:27,650 --> 00:35:28,700
(Blushing hard)

761
00:35:28,700 --> 00:35:30,650
I feel like his energy is very strong.

762
00:35:31,160 --> 00:35:33,100
(Paying attention)
And I tend to like being

763
00:35:33,100 --> 00:35:34,260
around positive people.

764
00:35:37,300 --> 00:35:37,790
Yeah.

765
00:35:38,840 --> 00:35:40,290
He was probably a bit nervous,

766
00:35:40,290 --> 00:35:44,160
so I squeezed his hand
to pass some energy to him

767
00:35:44,160 --> 00:35:45,960
and help him relax.

768
00:35:45,960 --> 00:35:47,500
He's probably still nervous now,

769
00:35:49,280 --> 00:35:52,270
but he's very cute
and full of positive energy.

770
00:35:52,270 --> 00:35:54,260
I think we'll work well together.

771
00:35:54,260 --> 00:35:55,130
Alright. No problem.

772
00:36:04,810 --> 00:36:06,790
♪Trying to be honest♪

773
00:36:06,790 --> 00:36:09,650
♪I'm not good at letting down my God♪

774
00:36:09,650 --> 00:36:14,730
♪I really want it,
for you I was running in the dark♪

775
00:36:14,730 --> 00:36:17,840
♪When you say this was goodbye♪

776
00:36:17,840 --> 00:36:20,260
When I looked at Jony,

777
00:36:20,260 --> 00:36:21,220
he's not someone who gets nervous,

778
00:36:21,220 --> 00:36:22,340
and

779
00:36:22,510 --> 00:36:23,830
he's a very confident person.

780
00:36:24,010 --> 00:36:24,900
Thank you.

781
00:36:25,230 --> 00:36:27,270
I also feel that

782
00:36:27,270 --> 00:36:28,790
he knows exactly what he wants.

783
00:36:28,790 --> 00:36:29,690
He's very goal-oriented.

784
00:36:29,960 --> 00:36:32,590
From his eyes,
I could see that he's very sincere.

785
00:36:32,590 --> 00:36:34,460
It felt like
he wasn't thinking about anything.

786
00:36:34,460 --> 00:36:35,610
He was just looking at me.

787
00:36:35,980 --> 00:36:37,370
But I don't know why he

788
00:36:37,370 --> 00:36:39,110
seemed very nervous
when he held my hand.

789
00:36:39,110 --> 00:36:41,440
His hand kept trembling,
and his ears turned a little red.

790
00:36:41,670 --> 00:36:43,430
Maybe he was shy.

791
00:36:45,370 --> 00:36:48,040
Actually, this was the first time

792
00:36:48,040 --> 00:36:51,080
we've looked at each other
for this long.

793
00:36:51,080 --> 00:36:54,900
Before this, we hadn't really gotten
to know each other deeply.

794
00:36:54,900 --> 00:36:59,990
It felt like the first time
I truly got to know him.

795
00:37:05,740 --> 00:37:08,570
When I looked at him,

796
00:37:08,570 --> 00:37:10,430
I also sensed a little regret.

797
00:37:10,430 --> 00:37:12,250
Because actually, Cannon really liked

798
00:37:12,250 --> 00:37:13,450
the Youyou script.

799
00:37:13,450 --> 00:37:16,330
But maybe
I didn't perform well enough today,

800
00:37:16,330 --> 00:37:17,920
(Blaming himself)
so he didn't get that script.

801
00:37:18,390 --> 00:37:20,030
No.

802
00:37:20,410 --> 00:37:21,070
No.

803
00:37:21,070 --> 00:37:23,470
When we looked at each other,

804
00:37:23,470 --> 00:37:25,380
I could sense he was a little unhappy,
just like now.

805
00:37:25,380 --> 00:37:26,380
Yes.

806
00:37:26,380 --> 00:37:27,180
(Admitting he feels upset)

807
00:37:27,580 --> 00:37:29,790
It's okay.

808
00:37:30,070 --> 00:37:31,450
It's okay.

809
00:37:32,990 --> 00:37:34,090
Thank you.

810
00:37:38,260 --> 00:37:40,120
Once filming starts,
you must give it your best.

811
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:43,220
Even if the problem isn't solved yet,

812
00:37:43,640 --> 00:37:44,800
when you perform,

813
00:37:44,800 --> 00:37:49,010
don't show your nervousness
to the audience.

814
00:37:50,160 --> 00:37:52,720
Because we are actors,

815
00:37:53,240 --> 00:37:56,520
our goal is to bring joy
to the audience.

816
00:37:56,520 --> 00:37:58,440
So no matter how upset we feel,

817
00:37:58,440 --> 00:38:02,280
the moment we step on stage,
try to leave those emotions behind

818
00:38:02,280 --> 00:38:03,860
and bring happiness to the audience.

819
00:38:04,730 --> 00:38:06,080
Everyone will experience this.

820
00:38:06,080 --> 00:38:09,100
Sometimes you really want a script
but you don't get it.

821
00:38:09,100 --> 00:38:11,700
But that doesn't mean
you're not good enough.

822
00:38:11,990 --> 00:38:13,270
Look at it positively.

823
00:38:13,270 --> 00:38:17,230
Maybe that script
just wasn't meant for you yet.

824
00:38:17,230 --> 00:38:18,640
So keep working hard.

825
00:38:19,050 --> 00:38:21,280
Give it your all.
Just like we always say,

826
00:38:21,280 --> 00:38:24,000
no matter what you do,
never lose your confidence.

827
00:38:35,470 --> 00:38:38,430
Everyone has now learned more
about their new partners.

828
00:38:38,430 --> 00:38:40,400
Next, we'll move on to the second game,

829
00:38:40,400 --> 00:38:42,000
scenario acting.

830
00:38:42,490 --> 00:38:44,610
(Chemistry Test Game 2: Scenario Acting)

831
00:38:44,880 --> 00:38:46,450
(Immediately raising hands)

832
00:38:47,700 --> 00:38:50,130
(Each team will go to the mentor
to receive a mission card.)

833
00:38:53,850 --> 00:38:56,700
(What task will the first group get?)

834
00:38:56,710 --> 00:38:57,880
(Scenario 1)

835
00:38:57,880 --> 00:38:59,340
Alright. Ready?

836
00:39:00,490 --> 00:39:02,820
Three, two, one, action.

837
00:39:02,870 --> 00:39:04,260
(A man collects a debt,
only to find it's his ex)

838
00:39:04,260 --> 00:39:05,630
(Tron as the debt collector,
Eugene as the ex)

839
00:39:05,630 --> 00:39:08,180
Hey! Pay your debt!

840
00:39:08,370 --> 00:39:08,990
Who is it?

841
00:39:10,190 --> 00:39:10,990
Open the door!

842
00:39:15,540 --> 00:39:17,620
Hey, open up!

843
00:39:18,580 --> 00:39:19,620
Long time no see.

844
00:39:21,490 --> 00:39:22,930
(Language barrier)

845
00:39:27,620 --> 00:39:28,450
Oh, it's you.

846
00:39:33,210 --> 00:39:34,650
You're here to collect the money?

847
00:39:35,150 --> 00:39:36,810
Yes, I came to collect the debt.

848
00:39:39,600 --> 00:39:40,770
How have you been?

849
00:39:46,680 --> 00:39:48,850
Just pay the money.
I don't really want to...

850
00:39:52,450 --> 00:39:53,390
Just pay the money.

851
00:39:59,870 --> 00:40:01,690
Alright. Let's pause there.

852
00:40:06,880 --> 00:40:08,890
I want everyone to remember

853
00:40:10,230 --> 00:40:11,930
that the lines
are not the most important thing.

854
00:40:12,140 --> 00:40:13,810
What matters most is the emotion.

855
00:40:13,810 --> 00:40:15,170
(Emotion matters more than dialogue)

856
00:40:15,670 --> 00:40:16,350
Understood?

857
00:40:16,490 --> 00:40:18,190
I'd like to add something.

858
00:40:18,550 --> 00:40:21,760
When we perform in front of people,

859
00:40:21,760 --> 00:40:22,730
if your voice

860
00:40:23,190 --> 00:40:24,510
isn't loud enough

861
00:40:24,510 --> 00:40:26,430
or your body language isn't clear,

862
00:40:26,430 --> 00:40:29,100
the audience won't understand
what you're acting.

863
00:40:29,400 --> 00:40:32,120
Try to speak loudly
and deliver your lines clearly.

864
00:40:32,120 --> 00:40:34,390
Or use stronger body language

865
00:40:34,390 --> 00:40:35,690
to help the audience
understand the story better.

866
00:40:37,770 --> 00:40:40,620
(Scenario 2: Spotting a celebrity
but forgetting who they are.)

867
00:40:40,620 --> 00:40:42,850
(Poom as the fan, Jony as the celebrity)

868
00:40:42,850 --> 00:40:43,990
Face the camera when you act.

869
00:40:45,380 --> 00:40:47,200
Are you a celebrity?

870
00:40:50,540 --> 00:40:52,410
Can I take a photo with you?

871
00:40:52,580 --> 00:40:53,210
Here.

872
00:40:53,960 --> 00:40:56,050
One, two, three.

873
00:40:57,530 --> 00:40:59,170
I'm so happy! I really like you.

874
00:40:59,170 --> 00:41:01,210
What projects do you have next?

875
00:41:01,350 --> 00:41:01,750
Yes.

876
00:41:01,750 --> 00:41:03,310
Is it a drama or something?

877
00:41:04,090 --> 00:41:04,720
Really?

878
00:41:05,960 --> 00:41:07,320
Could we get two more glasses of water?

879
00:41:08,720 --> 00:41:09,690
Here. Drink up.

880
00:41:10,950 --> 00:41:11,890
Thank you.

881
00:41:12,200 --> 00:41:13,350
Alright.

882
00:41:18,290 --> 00:41:19,950
(Scenario 3: A pet speaks
to its owner before dying)

883
00:41:19,950 --> 00:41:22,470
(Cannon as the owner)
My pet is about to die.

884
00:41:22,470 --> 00:41:25,790
(Pippin as the pet )
Judy.

885
00:41:26,520 --> 00:41:28,250
- Are you oka...
- I'm about to die.

886
00:41:30,380 --> 00:41:31,550
Why can you talk?

887
00:41:37,040 --> 00:41:37,570
No...

888
00:41:37,710 --> 00:41:40,480
In my next life,

889
00:41:40,480 --> 00:41:42,080
I hope I can still be your pet.

890
00:41:55,340 --> 00:41:56,100
Okay.

891
00:42:00,090 --> 00:42:02,600
(Scenario 4: Witnessing a body disposal
by the shore)

892
00:42:02,600 --> 00:42:04,270
(U.Jay as the fisherman)

893
00:42:04,270 --> 00:42:08,930
(Deaw as the killer)

894
00:42:28,950 --> 00:42:29,950
I've taken care of him.

895
00:42:31,340 --> 00:42:32,290
He's dead.

896
00:42:33,780 --> 00:42:35,610
Alright, I'm leaving now.

897
00:42:48,230 --> 00:42:49,460
Come on.

898
00:42:50,330 --> 00:42:51,170
(You give)

899
00:42:51,170 --> 00:42:53,060
(I won't)
Let them choose.

900
00:42:53,060 --> 00:42:53,690
Alright.

901
00:42:54,770 --> 00:42:55,170
Which one?

902
00:42:55,170 --> 00:42:56,730
Eeny, meeny, miny, moe...

903
00:42:57,120 --> 00:42:58,360
(Stop where it lands)

904
00:43:12,380 --> 00:43:13,870
(Scenario 5: After a class reunion,
you run into your first love.)

905
00:43:13,870 --> 00:43:15,210
(Tai as the male lead,
Ryu as the first love)

906
00:43:17,190 --> 00:43:18,230
(Help me out)
You...

907
00:43:18,230 --> 00:43:19,150
Look at me.

908
00:43:19,150 --> 00:43:19,950
I look at you?

909
00:43:19,950 --> 00:43:20,750
Yes, look at me.

910
00:43:20,750 --> 00:43:21,400
I look at you.

911
00:43:21,400 --> 00:43:22,070
You look at me.

912
00:43:22,370 --> 00:43:22,990
You sure?

913
00:43:26,110 --> 00:43:26,800
You sure?

914
00:43:27,050 --> 00:43:27,560
Sure!

915
00:43:27,800 --> 00:43:28,490
I look at you?

916
00:43:30,100 --> 00:43:32,230
(Language system malfunction)

917
00:43:32,230 --> 00:43:32,990
I look at you.

918
00:43:33,380 --> 00:43:34,130
I look at you.

919
00:43:34,560 --> 00:43:35,870
I look at you.

920
00:43:36,230 --> 00:43:36,920
You look at me.

921
00:43:36,920 --> 00:43:38,450
Okay.

922
00:43:38,900 --> 00:43:41,170
(Holding hands)

923
00:43:44,700 --> 00:43:48,620
The reunion just ends,
and I walk toward you,

924
00:43:48,620 --> 00:43:51,420
but I've had too much to drink.

925
00:43:54,210 --> 00:43:57,810
Then I see you and feel really happy.

926
00:43:57,810 --> 00:43:59,420
Then I...

927
00:44:00,680 --> 00:44:01,560
I...

928
00:44:03,290 --> 00:44:04,630
- Just improvise.
- Okay.

929
00:44:07,330 --> 00:44:09,650
Three, two, one, action.

930
00:44:09,890 --> 00:44:11,400
(Scenario 5: Reunion with first love)

931
00:44:11,400 --> 00:44:13,570
(Tai as the male lead,
Ryu as the first love)

932
00:44:16,060 --> 00:44:17,060
Thank you.

933
00:44:18,540 --> 00:44:19,260
Are you okay?

934
00:44:25,910 --> 00:44:26,900
Is that you, Tai?

935
00:44:28,330 --> 00:44:30,460
Ryu.

936
00:44:34,110 --> 00:44:34,840
Why are you so drunk?

937
00:44:34,840 --> 00:44:37,070
Ryu!

938
00:44:37,650 --> 00:44:40,180
I missed you so much.

939
00:44:42,420 --> 00:44:43,140
Tai...

940
00:44:44,190 --> 00:44:44,920
Tai...

941
00:44:46,430 --> 00:44:47,840
Why did I leave you?

942
00:44:48,260 --> 00:44:49,410
Why did you leave me?

943
00:44:52,430 --> 00:44:53,620
Oh my god.

944
00:44:58,190 --> 00:44:59,010
Why?

945
00:44:59,310 --> 00:45:00,400
That was a long time ago.

946
00:45:00,880 --> 00:45:01,440
And besides...

947
00:45:06,680 --> 00:45:08,170
(I can't watch)

948
00:45:08,170 --> 00:45:11,080
(Dying of laughter)

949
00:45:13,150 --> 00:45:15,010
Okay.

950
00:45:18,480 --> 00:45:20,050
(Scenario 6: Filing for divorce,
but the system crashes.)

951
00:45:20,050 --> 00:45:21,350
(Kai as the husband, Leo as the wife)

952
00:45:21,350 --> 00:45:22,590
You're late.

953
00:45:25,650 --> 00:45:26,250
Sorry.

954
00:45:26,250 --> 00:45:29,720
Forget it. Let's just get this done.

955
00:45:34,750 --> 00:45:35,310
Wait.

956
00:45:36,770 --> 00:45:37,750
Is there a problem?

957
00:45:38,980 --> 00:45:40,080
This is not happening!

958
00:45:41,780 --> 00:45:43,760
Never mind. It's fine.

959
00:45:46,610 --> 00:45:47,220
Thank you.

960
00:45:49,480 --> 00:45:50,700
Alright.

961
00:45:55,780 --> 00:45:58,720
Some of those scenes
were actually quite difficult to act.

962
00:45:59,080 --> 00:46:01,210
Each scenario
had a different level of difficulty.

963
00:46:01,210 --> 00:46:02,840
But what I want to say is

964
00:46:02,840 --> 00:46:05,600
everyone did their best.
You all did very well.

965
00:46:05,990 --> 00:46:08,840
However,
I want to remind everyone again.

966
00:46:10,070 --> 00:46:11,330
If you want to become an actor,

967
00:46:12,020 --> 00:46:12,980
you must act toward the camera.

968
00:46:14,530 --> 00:46:16,770
Several people kept turning their backs
to the camera.

969
00:46:17,410 --> 00:46:19,140
(Back facing the camera)

970
00:46:19,620 --> 00:46:21,010
(Back facing the camera)

971
00:46:21,290 --> 00:46:23,130
(Face not visible)

972
00:46:23,990 --> 00:46:26,470
When you perform, face the camera.

973
00:46:27,300 --> 00:46:29,010
The audience is here, not over there.

974
00:46:31,120 --> 00:46:31,750
So next time,

975
00:46:32,430 --> 00:46:35,970
or on the day of the actual performance,

976
00:46:35,970 --> 00:46:38,160
pay attention
to where the cameras are placed.

977
00:46:42,700 --> 00:46:44,970
As for me,
I think everyone did quite well.

978
00:46:44,970 --> 00:46:48,440
At least you all understood
what you were supposed to perform

979
00:46:48,440 --> 00:46:50,620
and managed
to convey it to the audience.

980
00:46:50,620 --> 00:46:53,720
I'd say you achieved about 80–90% of it.

981
00:46:53,720 --> 00:46:56,580
What I hope you learn from this is,

982
00:46:56,580 --> 00:46:57,510
every scenario

983
00:46:57,510 --> 00:47:02,390
is something we've experienced before

984
00:47:02,390 --> 00:47:05,390
or seen in real life,
and we're bringing that into acting.

985
00:47:05,760 --> 00:47:08,200
For example,
in the divorce scene just now,

986
00:47:08,370 --> 00:47:09,710
all it takes is signing a paper
and handing it over,

987
00:47:09,710 --> 00:47:11,940
and everyone can immediately tell
it was a divorce.

988
00:47:11,940 --> 00:47:13,020
Sometimes,

989
00:47:13,610 --> 00:47:15,150
small details

990
00:47:15,150 --> 00:47:18,020
can help convey the story
to the audience

991
00:47:18,020 --> 00:47:21,800
and help them understand
what we're trying to convey.

992
00:47:22,310 --> 00:47:24,130
If you want to practice,

993
00:47:24,130 --> 00:47:27,830
imagine what you would do
in that situation,

994
00:47:27,830 --> 00:47:29,490
or how it's performed
in the movies you like.

995
00:47:29,490 --> 00:47:30,440
That will help a lot.

996
00:47:31,330 --> 00:47:31,930
So now,

997
00:47:31,930 --> 00:47:35,120
please practice
your new scripts seriously.

998
00:47:35,350 --> 00:47:39,350
We will have the final evaluation
in two days.

999
00:47:39,500 --> 00:47:40,850
Alright.

1000
00:47:41,560 --> 00:47:43,510
Thank you.

1001
00:47:43,510 --> 00:47:44,890
Thank you, teacher.

1002
00:47:52,550 --> 00:47:55,130
(One day before filming)

1003
00:47:55,430 --> 00:47:58,460
After yesterday's regrouping
and script selection,

1004
00:47:59,080 --> 00:48:00,630
today marks the day before filming.

1005
00:48:00,630 --> 00:48:02,550
(Everyone studies their script)
Mentor training and group rehearsals.

1006
00:48:03,420 --> 00:48:05,570
(Advanced Acting Workshop: Fort X Peat)

1007
00:48:05,570 --> 00:48:06,520
"Yin-Yang Fate"

1008
00:48:06,520 --> 00:48:07,570
(Kai X Leo / Ryu X Tai)

1009
00:48:07,570 --> 00:48:08,490
"The CEO Falls for Me"

1010
00:48:08,490 --> 00:48:09,410
(U.Jay X Deaw / Jony X Poom)

1011
00:48:09,410 --> 00:48:10,600
"Galaxy Garden"

1012
00:48:10,600 --> 00:48:11,530
(Eugene X Tron / Cannon X Pippin)

1013
00:48:11,530 --> 00:48:13,530
Hello.

1014
00:48:13,600 --> 00:48:17,050
Hello.

1015
00:48:17,630 --> 00:48:19,290
(Actors in position)
Alright.

1016
00:48:19,650 --> 00:48:23,250
Everyone should have a basic grasp
of the characters and plot.

1017
00:48:23,250 --> 00:48:24,910
Have you all memorized your lines?

1018
00:48:25,570 --> 00:48:27,310
(Shy)

1019
00:48:27,850 --> 00:48:28,850
Not completely yet.

1020
00:48:28,850 --> 00:48:30,420
We might not remember them clearly.

1021
00:48:30,420 --> 00:48:32,030
(Remembered a little)
But we've been trying.

1022
00:48:32,030 --> 00:48:35,520
- Alright. Let's do it.
- Cover it.

1023
00:48:35,520 --> 00:48:36,340
Don't worry about the lines.

1024
00:48:36,340 --> 00:48:37,980
- Cover it.
- For me, the lines aren't important.

1025
00:48:37,980 --> 00:48:38,850
Let's cover it for now.

1026
00:48:40,840 --> 00:48:44,060
We'll just do a trial performance today.

1027
00:48:44,290 --> 00:48:45,260
Okay.

1028
00:48:46,470 --> 00:48:47,280
Alright.

1029
00:48:47,670 --> 00:48:48,330
Alright.

1030
00:48:48,510 --> 00:48:49,140
You go first, okay?

1031
00:48:49,140 --> 00:48:49,710
Okay.

1032
00:48:49,950 --> 00:48:50,630
Good luck.

1033
00:48:50,980 --> 00:48:51,770
Good luck!

1034
00:48:52,380 --> 00:48:53,620
"Galaxy Garden"
(Group rehearsal)

1035
00:48:53,620 --> 00:48:54,890
(Actors: Eugene / Tron /
Cannon / Pippin)

1036
00:48:54,890 --> 00:48:58,080
(Pippin as Baicai, Cannon as Dao Mingwu)
One, two, three.

1037
00:48:58,080 --> 00:48:58,760
Action!

1038
00:48:58,880 --> 00:49:02,660
"Galaxy Garden"

1039
00:49:03,330 --> 00:49:04,300
Are you out of your mind?

1040
00:49:04,300 --> 00:49:05,270
Why are you here?

1041
00:49:07,040 --> 00:49:09,550
Now you remember to care about me?

1042
00:49:09,550 --> 00:49:10,700
Get up first.

1043
00:49:12,990 --> 00:49:14,030
Don't touch me.

1044
00:49:14,480 --> 00:49:16,110
Didn't you say
you didn't want to meet me?

1045
00:49:17,010 --> 00:49:19,570
(Recording feedback)

1046
00:49:23,960 --> 00:49:24,750
You must be hungry.

1047
00:49:24,750 --> 00:49:26,290
Let's go. I'll treat you to a meal.

1048
00:49:28,530 --> 00:49:30,170
Come on, don't be mad.

1049
00:49:30,170 --> 00:49:30,860
Let's go together.

1050
00:49:34,350 --> 00:49:35,610
Very good. It's fine.

1051
00:49:37,390 --> 00:49:38,280
Alright.

1052
00:49:38,400 --> 00:49:42,320
From what I see,
both groups were acting quite well.

1053
00:49:42,790 --> 00:49:43,630
(Happy)

1054
00:49:43,630 --> 00:49:45,590
For your group,
the pace should be slower.

1055
00:49:45,590 --> 00:49:46,610
(Slow down the pace)

1056
00:49:46,610 --> 00:49:47,250
Slow it down.

1057
00:49:47,540 --> 00:49:50,200
Just now it felt a little too fast.

1058
00:49:51,240 --> 00:49:53,560
Also, something I want
to tell both groups is

1059
00:49:53,560 --> 00:49:54,190
when we're performing,

1060
00:49:54,390 --> 00:49:55,690
don't let the audience feel like

1061
00:49:55,690 --> 00:49:58,300
(Don't reveal the plot too early)
you know what's going to happen.

1062
00:49:58,470 --> 00:49:59,730
If they sense that, they'll think,

1063
00:49:59,730 --> 00:50:01,500
"Oh, this is what's coming next".

1064
00:50:01,700 --> 00:50:03,930
And we won't be able
to convey the emotions properly.

1065
00:50:04,260 --> 00:50:06,930
First hear it. Next smell it.

1066
00:50:06,930 --> 00:50:08,950
(Hear it. Smell it. See it.)
Then see it. Finally act.

1067
00:50:08,950 --> 00:50:10,850
(React naturally)
Take it step by step.

1068
00:50:11,910 --> 00:50:14,570
It's actually very simple.

1069
00:50:14,770 --> 00:50:19,370
Acting is like playing ping-pong.

1070
00:50:19,380 --> 00:50:21,130
(Ping-pong?)

1071
00:50:21,130 --> 00:50:24,290
(Advanced Acting Workshop: Fort X Peat)

1072
00:50:24,290 --> 00:50:27,330
For example, if you want
to portray Baicai's part better,

1073
00:50:27,740 --> 00:50:29,230
she is just walking over

1074
00:50:30,180 --> 00:50:32,270
(Focused)
to throw away the trash.

1075
00:50:32,780 --> 00:50:34,290
She has no idea
someone is standing there.

1076
00:50:34,290 --> 00:50:36,210
Then she turns around
and suddenly sees him.

1077
00:50:37,440 --> 00:50:39,080
(Understand the situation first)
Her first thought should be

1078
00:50:39,080 --> 00:50:41,190
who that is.
Not just rush straight over.

1079
00:50:42,020 --> 00:50:43,690
(Did you get it?)

1080
00:50:43,830 --> 00:50:45,400
She wonders what he's doing.

1081
00:50:45,400 --> 00:50:46,720
Then she rushes over to check.

1082
00:50:47,550 --> 00:50:48,450
(Checking the character again)
Why is he standing here?

1083
00:50:48,450 --> 00:50:49,330
What is he doing here?

1084
00:50:49,330 --> 00:50:50,270
Then she holds the umbrella for him.

1085
00:50:51,240 --> 00:50:51,910
Can you picture that?

1086
00:50:51,910 --> 00:50:53,650
It has to be performed step by step.

1087
00:50:53,650 --> 00:50:54,540
Step by step.

1088
00:50:57,670 --> 00:50:59,050
"The CEO Falls for Me"
(Group performance)

1089
00:50:59,050 --> 00:51:00,090
(Actors: U.Jay / Deaw / Jony / Poom)

1090
00:51:00,090 --> 00:51:03,980
(Deaw as Lin / U.Jay as President Gu)
Three, two, one.

1091
00:51:03,980 --> 00:51:04,630
Action.

1092
00:51:04,630 --> 00:51:15,480
"The CEO Falls for Me"

1093
00:51:15,480 --> 00:51:16,130
Mr. Gu!

1094
00:51:16,960 --> 00:51:17,610
Mr. Gu!

1095
00:51:21,600 --> 00:51:22,270
Mr. Gu!

1096
00:51:22,280 --> 00:51:24,330
(Controlling the scene)

1097
00:51:28,300 --> 00:51:29,170
President Gu!
