01:02:06,130 --> 01:02:08,380
Should we skip a couple of steps?

1366
01:02:08,380 --> 01:02:08,930
Okay.

1367
01:02:13,850 --> 01:02:15,330
(Naturally holding hands)

1368
01:02:15,330 --> 01:02:17,200
Alright. Let's try again.

1369
01:02:18,270 --> 01:02:18,710
Okay.

1370
01:02:18,710 --> 01:02:19,740
Being with him

1371
01:02:19,740 --> 01:02:21,650
(Happy to be partners)
just makes me happy.

1372
01:02:21,650 --> 01:02:23,690
He gives his best effort,

1373
01:02:23,690 --> 01:02:25,650
and I give mine.

1374
01:02:25,650 --> 01:02:27,420
Whether it's good or bad,
it doesn't matter.

1375
01:02:28,210 --> 01:02:31,690
I think everyone should give their best.

1376
01:02:31,690 --> 01:02:32,670
I think...

1377
01:02:32,670 --> 01:02:36,120
Okay. This is good.

1378
01:02:36,120 --> 01:02:36,880
Not bad.

1379
01:02:36,880 --> 01:02:39,220
We won't say we're the best,
but we definitely won't be bad.

1380
01:02:40,270 --> 01:02:42,210
As for acting and singing,

1381
01:02:42,210 --> 01:02:45,620
I think I'm actually
quite strong at both.

1382
01:02:45,980 --> 01:02:47,130
(Confident)

1383
01:02:47,130 --> 01:02:49,370
("The CEO Falls for Me" - Jony & Poom)
One, two, three. Action.

1384
01:02:53,040 --> 01:02:54,160
Feels like we're running out of time.

1385
01:02:55,180 --> 01:02:56,260
Oh my, President Gu!

1386
01:02:56,900 --> 01:02:58,510
Gu, are you okay?

1387
01:02:58,510 --> 01:03:00,520
(One person playing two roles)

1388
01:03:02,040 --> 01:03:03,590
Who...

1389
01:03:03,590 --> 01:03:05,590
(A bit stiff)
Who saved me?

1390
01:03:08,490 --> 01:03:10,880
President Gu, don't you hate that woman?

1391
01:03:11,100 --> 01:03:13,020
I'll deal with her for you.

1392
01:03:13,020 --> 01:03:14,370
(Worried)

1393
01:03:14,370 --> 01:03:17,230
I'm confident
because this is what I'm best at.

1394
01:03:17,360 --> 01:03:18,030
But...

1395
01:03:18,230 --> 01:03:19,010
What are you doing?

1396
01:03:19,010 --> 01:03:21,110
If I watch his performance,

1397
01:03:21,110 --> 01:03:21,660
then...

1398
01:03:22,740 --> 01:03:23,700
it's over.

1399
01:03:25,100 --> 01:03:25,890
Worried?

1400
01:03:26,130 --> 01:03:27,370
(Worried +1)

1401
01:03:27,370 --> 01:03:30,810
Actually, the most challenging part

1402
01:03:30,810 --> 01:03:32,280
is the acting.

1403
01:03:32,280 --> 01:03:35,000
I get nervous because I don't know
how it will turn out.

1404
01:03:35,000 --> 01:03:38,430
Especially when one person speaks Thai
and the other speaks Chinese.

1405
01:03:39,090 --> 01:03:41,020
("The CEO Falls for Me" - U.Jay & Deaw)
Alright, I'm Ouyang.

1406
01:03:41,020 --> 01:03:41,650
Okay.

1407
01:03:42,210 --> 01:03:43,070
You're Lin.

1408
01:03:43,070 --> 01:03:43,660
Okay.

1409
01:03:47,210 --> 01:03:48,260
Fifty million.

1410
01:03:48,820 --> 01:03:49,780
Leave President Gu.

1411
01:03:50,390 --> 01:03:51,710
What kind of person do you think I am?

1412
01:03:51,950 --> 01:03:53,590
Not enough?

1413
01:03:55,330 --> 01:03:56,180
One hundred million.

1414
01:03:56,180 --> 01:03:57,050
Ouyang,

1415
01:03:57,200 --> 01:03:58,840
I'm just President Gu's friend.

1416
01:03:59,530 --> 01:04:00,430
Friend?

1417
01:04:01,200 --> 01:04:02,130
Do you think you deserve it?

1418
01:04:02,210 --> 01:04:04,450
A maid earning forty-five an hour.

1419
01:04:04,650 --> 01:04:06,040
It went up to fifty yesterday.

1420
01:04:06,500 --> 01:04:07,510
One hundred million.

1421
01:04:08,540 --> 01:04:10,070
Why don't you just
take the money and leave?

1422
01:04:10,070 --> 01:04:11,630
Acting high and mighty, huh?

1423
01:04:18,460 --> 01:04:20,000
(To be continued)
Okay.

1424
01:04:20,000 --> 01:04:20,790
Understood?

1425
01:04:20,790 --> 01:04:21,390
Understood.

1426
01:04:21,390 --> 01:04:21,950
(Very happy)

1427
01:04:21,950 --> 01:04:22,710
Okay.

1428
01:04:22,810 --> 01:04:23,630
I'm thinking

1429
01:04:23,630 --> 01:04:27,430
about which language
we should use for the performance.

1430
01:04:28,100 --> 01:04:29,880
I want to try Thai

1431
01:04:29,880 --> 01:04:32,440
because I feel like
my lines aren't that many,

1432
01:04:32,440 --> 01:04:34,480
so I should be able to memorize them.

1433
01:04:34,680 --> 01:04:37,390
But I've never acted in Thai before,

1434
01:04:37,390 --> 01:04:38,460
so I'm not sure

1435
01:04:38,460 --> 01:04:42,080
(Hesitating)
whether I can handle the role well.

1436
01:04:42,190 --> 01:04:42,770
You can do it.

1437
01:04:43,030 --> 01:04:45,330
(Encouraging)
Let's try performing it in Thai first.

1438
01:04:45,330 --> 01:04:47,190
If Thai doesn't work,

1439
01:04:47,190 --> 01:04:48,910
we can switch to another language later.

1440
01:04:49,780 --> 01:04:50,400
Okay.

1441
01:04:50,400 --> 01:04:51,150
Let's try it.

1442
01:04:51,150 --> 01:04:52,440
Alright.

1443
01:04:52,440 --> 01:04:54,430
I'm someone who finds it difficult
to make choices.

1444
01:04:54,430 --> 01:04:55,670
Sometimes I hesitate a lot.

1445
01:04:55,670 --> 01:04:57,620
But when someone gives me
a clear direction,

1446
01:04:58,150 --> 01:05:00,100
it helps me decide quickly.

1447
01:05:01,630 --> 01:05:03,200
What's this in Thai?

1448
01:05:03,540 --> 01:05:04,190
Who.

1449
01:05:04,460 --> 01:05:05,010
Who.

1450
01:05:05,010 --> 01:05:05,600
Yeah.

1451
01:05:05,600 --> 01:05:06,750
Who saved me?

1452
01:05:07,040 --> 01:05:07,650
Me?

1453
01:05:07,650 --> 01:05:08,130
Yeah.

1454
01:05:08,340 --> 01:05:09,160
Me.

1455
01:05:10,000 --> 01:05:11,860
What right do you have to do this?

1456
01:05:12,410 --> 01:05:15,390
What right do you have
to treat Lin like that?

1457
01:05:15,570 --> 01:05:16,210
Yeah.

1458
01:05:16,850 --> 01:05:19,000
Don't go too far.

1459
01:05:19,610 --> 01:05:23,080
What right do you have
to treat Lin like that?

1460
01:05:23,080 --> 01:05:25,170
Don't go too far.

1461
01:05:25,170 --> 01:05:25,640
Yeah.

1462
01:05:26,960 --> 01:05:27,920
That day...

1463
01:05:28,470 --> 01:05:29,670
That day...

1464
01:05:30,310 --> 01:05:30,990
I...

1465
01:05:31,190 --> 01:05:31,990
I...

1466
01:05:31,990 --> 01:05:33,890
Or should I say... I*?
[*the male pronoun]

1467
01:05:33,890 --> 01:05:34,640
Would that work?

1468
01:05:34,640 --> 01:05:36,690
That's better.

1469
01:05:36,690 --> 01:05:37,840
Oh, I...

1470
01:05:39,250 --> 01:05:40,650
The day I fell into the water...

1471
01:05:41,930 --> 01:05:42,660
U.Jay.

1472
01:05:42,700 --> 01:05:44,870
(Jony and Poom join them)
Let's rehearse together.

1473
01:05:44,870 --> 01:05:45,730
Okay.

1474
01:05:45,730 --> 01:05:47,950
How about this? Let's make the story
a double male lead.

1475
01:05:47,950 --> 01:05:49,020
(Two domineering CEOs?)

1476
01:05:49,020 --> 01:05:50,690
Are you serious?

1477
01:05:50,690 --> 01:05:51,840
We can rewrite the plot.

1478
01:05:51,840 --> 01:05:52,680
(Creative sparks flying)
Really?

1479
01:05:52,680 --> 01:05:53,710
That sounds exciting.

1480
01:05:54,330 --> 01:05:56,120
We perform our own scenes first,

1481
01:05:56,120 --> 01:05:57,190
then we merge them together.

1482
01:05:57,190 --> 01:05:57,770
Sure.

1483
01:05:57,770 --> 01:05:59,150
Okay, so now for this...

1484
01:06:01,380 --> 01:06:02,330
What are you guys doing?

1485
01:06:02,330 --> 01:06:04,150
(Laughing)

1486
01:06:04,150 --> 01:06:06,570
Why would you treat Ouyang like that?

1487
01:06:06,880 --> 01:06:08,140
I never expected

1488
01:06:08,140 --> 01:06:09,280
you'd be that kind of person.

1489
01:06:09,280 --> 01:06:11,350
Then what kind of person
does President Gu think I am?

1490
01:06:12,440 --> 01:06:13,480
It was you.

1491
01:06:14,030 --> 01:06:14,810
(What happened?)

1492
01:06:14,810 --> 01:06:17,250
You took the place of my savior.

1493
01:06:18,040 --> 01:06:20,950
So all this time,

1494
01:06:21,470 --> 01:06:22,950
you've been deceiving me
and gaining my trust.

1495
01:06:23,130 --> 01:06:25,910
(Trying not to laugh)

1496
01:06:32,630 --> 01:06:33,300
Oh my,

1497
01:06:33,590 --> 01:06:34,330
President Gu!

1498
01:06:34,820 --> 01:06:35,640
Are you okay?

1499
01:06:36,090 --> 01:06:36,880
Who?

1500
01:06:37,540 --> 01:06:38,430
Who saved me?

1501
01:06:38,430 --> 01:06:39,510
Of course it was me.

1502
01:06:39,860 --> 01:06:41,130
I heard someone fall into the water,

1503
01:06:41,130 --> 01:06:42,190
so I came to save you.

1504
01:06:42,830 --> 01:06:44,490
One hundred million. Sign it.

1505
01:06:44,910 --> 01:06:45,750
Move out tonight.

1506
01:06:46,390 --> 01:06:47,920
It's not easy being
at the Gu residence.

1507
01:06:48,060 --> 01:06:49,140
If you don't leave now,

1508
01:06:49,430 --> 01:06:50,140
he'll find out...

1509
01:06:50,930 --> 01:06:52,930
he'll find out
about what happened that night.

1510
01:06:55,510 --> 01:06:56,780
(Trying to calm down)
Find out what?

1511
01:06:59,310 --> 01:07:00,670
President Gu!

1512
01:07:00,990 --> 01:07:02,200
(What's going on?)

1513
01:07:02,200 --> 01:07:04,610
Whether I tried to hide it
or deceive you just now,

1514
01:07:04,610 --> 01:07:07,350
I still couldn't earn a place of trust
by your side.

1515
01:07:11,540 --> 01:07:12,200
Okay.

1516
01:07:13,090 --> 01:07:14,810
I think my acting was pretty good.

1517
01:07:15,210 --> 01:07:16,360
I'm willing to go all out.

1518
01:07:16,820 --> 01:07:18,300
I can be bold

1519
01:07:18,300 --> 01:07:19,920
but also gentle when needed.

1520
01:07:20,210 --> 01:07:21,170
Maybe it's just natural talent.

1521
01:07:21,410 --> 01:07:24,580
When I was young, I always wanted
to go Hengdian to be an extra.

1522
01:07:24,860 --> 01:07:26,590
But when I got there,
I didn't become an extra

1523
01:07:26,590 --> 01:07:27,730
and went straight
to being the male lead.

1524
01:07:28,230 --> 01:07:29,870
(Proud smile)

1525
01:07:30,220 --> 01:07:31,150
What are you laughing at?

1526
01:07:31,150 --> 01:07:32,890
I'm going to get serious in a moment.

1527
01:07:32,890 --> 01:07:34,530
(Strong yet gentle)
I need to protect my CEO image.

1528
01:07:35,240 --> 01:07:36,360
Oh my goodness.

1529
01:07:36,750 --> 01:07:38,900
Jony is actually a very funny person.

1530
01:07:39,300 --> 01:07:41,620
But honestly,
I feel like I've already won.

1531
01:07:41,620 --> 01:07:43,600
At least in Mandarin.

1532
01:07:45,170 --> 01:07:46,320
No, that's not what I meant.

1533
01:07:46,320 --> 01:07:48,560
Actually my weakness
is remembering lines.

1534
01:07:48,990 --> 01:07:50,960
For everything else,
like the acting itself,

1535
01:07:50,960 --> 01:07:52,660
I'm pretty good.

1536
01:07:53,330 --> 01:07:55,480
I said, if you don't believe me,
come and compete with me.

1537
01:07:55,480 --> 01:07:56,870
Then we'll see the real skills
in action.

1538
01:07:56,870 --> 01:07:57,680
(Rival comes for CEO)

1539
01:07:57,680 --> 01:08:00,010
When it comes to acting, I'm not afraid.

1540
01:08:00,020 --> 01:08:00,820
(Not afraid)

1541
01:08:01,160 --> 01:08:01,650
Is that okay?

1542
01:08:01,650 --> 01:08:02,960
Do you want to play Ouyang?

1543
01:08:02,960 --> 01:08:03,520
Fine with anything.

1544
01:08:03,520 --> 01:08:04,680
Ask him if he wants to.

1545
01:08:04,680 --> 01:08:05,450
No.

1546
01:08:05,450 --> 01:08:07,260
(No)
No.

1547
01:08:07,350 --> 01:08:08,770
No, no. Okay.

1548
01:08:08,830 --> 01:08:11,870
Aren't you going to speak Thai then?

1549
01:08:12,270 --> 01:08:14,850
If he helps you play Ouyang,
that might work better.

1550
01:08:14,850 --> 01:08:15,850
But he doesn't want to.

1551
01:08:16,150 --> 01:08:17,440
He doesn't want to play Ouyang.

1552
01:08:17,640 --> 01:08:19,110
(Doesn't want to play Ouyang)

1553
01:08:19,110 --> 01:08:21,810
Actually, President Gu doesn't
have that many lines.

1554
01:08:21,810 --> 01:08:22,620
Do you want to try learning them?

1555
01:08:22,620 --> 01:08:23,660
Since the lines are short,

1556
01:08:23,660 --> 01:08:24,450
they're easy to memorize.

1557
01:08:24,670 --> 01:08:26,800
If both Ouyang roles speak Thai,

1558
01:08:26,800 --> 01:08:27,730
only the two of them can do it.

1559
01:08:27,730 --> 01:08:29,750
(Suggesting Deaw and Poom
play Ouyang again)

1560
01:08:30,900 --> 01:08:32,690
Because the two of us might need

1561
01:08:32,690 --> 01:08:33,990
(U.Jay explaining)
to perform in Thai.

1562
01:08:33,990 --> 01:08:35,130
Ouyang's lines

1563
01:08:35,130 --> 01:08:37,490
would be too much if he spoke them

1564
01:08:37,630 --> 01:08:38,480
in Thai,

1565
01:08:38,480 --> 01:08:41,380
so maybe Poom can play Ouyang in Thai.

1566
01:08:41,940 --> 01:08:44,400
That means your script will be in Thai.

1567
01:08:44,880 --> 01:08:46,110
(Poom agrees)
Okay, that works.

1568
01:08:47,020 --> 01:08:50,610
Alright. I think we should all
try it once in Thai.

1569
01:08:50,610 --> 01:08:51,340
(Confused)

1570
01:08:51,340 --> 01:08:52,950
Did you discuss that with Poom?

1571
01:08:52,950 --> 01:08:54,150
About everyone speaking Thai?

1572
01:08:54,150 --> 01:08:55,940
(Miscommunication)
I... Actually...

1573
01:08:55,940 --> 01:08:56,620
Can you translate for him?

1574
01:08:56,620 --> 01:08:57,630
I can learn the Thai lines

1575
01:08:57,630 --> 01:08:58,670
because there aren't many.

1576
01:08:58,670 --> 01:08:59,580
We can give it a try.

1577
01:08:59,580 --> 01:09:02,710
Does that mean I speak Thai,
and he speaks Chinese?

1578
01:09:02,710 --> 01:09:03,110
No, no.

1579
01:09:03,110 --> 01:09:04,200
I'll speak Thai.

1580
01:09:04,200 --> 01:09:05,110
I wish to give it a try.

1581
01:09:05,110 --> 01:09:05,890
(Compromise)

1582
01:09:05,890 --> 01:09:09,420
To be honest,
he's a very confident person.

1583
01:09:09,420 --> 01:09:11,690
(Emergency Thai practice)
Who saved me?

1584
01:09:11,820 --> 01:09:13,660
Who... Who...

1585
01:09:14,190 --> 01:09:15,400
Saved me.

1586
01:09:15,400 --> 01:09:16,710
Saved.

1587
01:09:17,330 --> 01:09:18,060
Saved.

1588
01:09:22,590 --> 01:09:33,650
What right do you have
to treat Lin like this?

1589
01:09:33,650 --> 01:09:36,040
No.

1590
01:09:37,970 --> 01:09:40,380
That line can be in Chinese.

1591
01:09:40,390 --> 01:09:41,350
This is too hard.

1592
01:09:41,350 --> 01:09:42,050
I'll say it in Chinese.

1593
01:09:42,050 --> 01:09:44,390
(Decides to use Chinese)
You took the place of my savior.

1594
01:09:44,530 --> 01:09:45,570
This line is too long.

1595
01:09:45,570 --> 01:09:50,570
You took the place
of my savior.

1596
01:09:53,520 --> 01:09:54,530
I like this.

1597
01:09:54,530 --> 01:09:55,740
- Do you like this one?
- Yeah.

1598
01:09:55,740 --> 01:09:56,730
We can rewrite the plot.

1599
01:09:56,730 --> 01:09:58,860
If both Ouyang roles speak Thai,

1600
01:09:58,860 --> 01:09:59,490
only they can do it.

1601
01:09:59,490 --> 01:10:01,370
Let's just perform everything in Thai.

1602
01:10:01,370 --> 01:10:02,350
Then I'll just use Chinese.

1603
01:10:05,250 --> 01:10:06,030
I'm a bit...

1604
01:10:11,680 --> 01:10:13,120
I'm good at acting,

1605
01:10:13,430 --> 01:10:16,430
but if I have to work with someone
I don't get along with,

1606
01:10:16,430 --> 01:10:17,270
I can't do it.

1607
01:10:18,040 --> 01:10:19,880
(Completely unaware)
Everything seemed fine all day though.

1608
01:10:20,550 --> 01:10:21,600
Acting...

1609
01:10:22,270 --> 01:10:25,160
He arrogantly says he's acted before.

1610
01:10:25,160 --> 01:10:26,400
I'm perfect for the CEO role.

1611
01:10:26,400 --> 01:10:27,200
I act really well.

1612
01:10:27,530 --> 01:10:30,070
I'm good with the aura, the expressions,

1613
01:10:30,190 --> 01:10:31,730
and the body language.

1614
01:10:32,090 --> 01:10:34,780
I entered this industry
when I was fourteen.

1615
01:10:35,590 --> 01:10:36,730
I've seen all kinds of people,

1616
01:10:36,730 --> 01:10:37,900
but I've never seen anyone like him.

1617
01:10:37,900 --> 01:10:39,400
I think he's

1618
01:10:39,730 --> 01:10:40,440
just a young boy.

1619
01:10:40,440 --> 01:10:42,040
Sometimes he's very shy.

1620
01:10:42,230 --> 01:10:44,800
From my perspective,
his acting feels childish.

1621
01:10:45,040 --> 01:10:46,930
He kept praising me for being confident.

1622
01:10:46,930 --> 01:10:48,970
But his acting

1623
01:10:48,970 --> 01:10:49,740
that's about it.

1624
01:10:49,740 --> 01:10:51,310
He's too confident.

1625
01:10:51,310 --> 01:10:55,210
We showed each other
some clips of our past acting work.

1626
01:10:55,670 --> 01:10:58,170
We both thought we did pretty well.

1627
01:10:58,960 --> 01:11:00,880
But I didn't think
he was that impressive.

1628
01:11:00,880 --> 01:11:02,890
Working with him is quite difficult.

1629
01:11:03,650 --> 01:11:05,690
I feel like I can't win this round.

1630
01:11:06,310 --> 01:11:07,950
So maybe we just need more time
to adjust.

1631
01:11:08,310 --> 01:11:11,570
It's not even
about understanding each other anymore.

1632
01:11:11,570 --> 01:11:12,690
It feels more like

1633
01:11:14,100 --> 01:11:14,870
